						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">fzero</div><br />Awesome.<br /><br />Whether or not it will make executable size optimizations based on various properties (static, const, initialized, etc.) is up to the compiler, it's not defined in the spec, I don't think. I've never seen a compiler put an uninitialized static array in the executable (and I wouldn't expect it), but it's technically allowed, just like GCC is apparently allowed to optimize away 0-fill initializations.</div>

